main event: A circular blue-green object was observed for 1 hour in Kew Gardens, New York, before disappearing into the north.
interesting points: The object was stationary and not identified as a star despite being viewed through a telescope and compass,The observation lasted for an hour before the object disappeared,The report concluded the sighting was of Mars, no physical evidence was recorded or photographs taken, The object was described as 10 feet long and dark in color, traveling at an estimated speed of 500-600 mph.
witness description: civilian observer using telescope and compass
